      {
        "id": "872c715f3f9576e1b63a66c57c98d920de9b8c77",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 7680,
          "name": "Renu Kumari",
          "display_name": "Renu Kumari",
          "email": "kashi.renu@gmail.com",
          "username": "renukumari"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2021-09-03 12:20:44.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n> \n> From what I understand,if AsyncConfig and notificationExecutor bean are not laoded by Spring then processDataUpdatedEvent form NotificationService is simply execusted synchronously.\n> \n>     @Async(\"notificationExecutor\")\n>     public Future<Void> processDataUpdatedEvent(...)\n> \n> Am I correct ?\n\n@EnableAsync is required to run method marked as @Async. If AsyncConfig is not loaded, then @EnableAsync is not enabled and @Async annotation is ignored.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "49da8ff558c5645e994cbe3d9d318c9a398607d1",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5658,
          "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
          "username": "brusak"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-09-03 12:23:04.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> > Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n> > \n> > From what I understand,if AsyncConfig and notificationExecutor bean are not laoded by Spring then processDataUpdatedEvent form NotificationService is simply execusted synchronously.\n> > \n> >     @Async(\"notificationExecutor\")\n> >     public Future<Void> processDataUpdatedEvent(...)\n> > \n> > Am I correct ?\n> \n> @EnableAsync is required to run method marked as @Async. If AsyncConfig is not loaded, then @EnableAsync is not enabled and @Async annotation is ignored.\n\nGood, thanks.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
